This topic describes the firewall ports and protocols requirements for using Pivotal Container Service (PKS) on vSphere with NSX-T integration.

In environments with strict inter-network access control policies, firewalls often require conduits to pass communication between system components 
on a different network or allow interfacing with external systems such as with enterprise applications or the public Internet. 

